entries.tatooine_vistas_01: From this vantage point, the city known as a wretched hive of scum and villainy, looks very peaceful.
entries.tatooine_vistas_02: Located near the center of the Tatooine world map; this location, when viewed from above, looks similar to the work of D.M. Skecher.
entries.tatooine_vistas_03: Although Tatooine has few plains, and little vegetation for grazing; some locals make their living working a ranch.  With the view from this patio, it's easy to see why.
entries.tatooine_vistas_04: One of the few Oases on Tatooine, Imperials settled near this one to ensure they had a plentiful supply of water.
entries.tatooine_vistas_05: From high above, looking down on this defensive stronghold, it looks as much a prison as a fortress.
entries.tatooine_vistas_06: This structure, although filled with crime, filth and torturous deeds inside, is an architectural wonder from the outside.
entries.tatooine_vistas_07: South of the what some refer to as the Graveyard, the body of water in this Oasis is often mistaken as a mirage, given its near-perfect circular shape.
entries.tatooine_vistas_08: Biggs often sat and pondered here while growing up. His home in the distance; picking his place among the stars.
entries.tatooine_vistas_09: No ordinary graveyard, this is home to some of the most fierce creatures in the Galaxy.  Keep your distance, or they could leave this world with a full stomach.
entries.tatooine_vistas_10: A wise hermit, once a great warrior, resides in this location.  Having seen much more than any ordinary citizen, this hermit chose this rural location to find some rest and relaxation.
